{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Ban employers & recruiters asking about candidates\u2019 salaries when recruiting",
        "additional_details": "We believe a person\u2019s salary history reflects past circumstances, not their skills or suitability for a role. Allowing employers to ask this question could lock people into lower pay and carry forward past underpayment throughout their careers. This affects workers at all wage levels and may limit fair pay progression. Banning salary-history questions could support fairer recruitment and ensure pay is based on the role and the candidate\u2019s capability.",
        "background": "Change employment laws so that employers and recruiters are prohibited from asking candidates about their current or previous salary at any stage of the recruitment process.",
